# Wellfit QA — Slack message tone

When Chris asks for a **Slack message** (ping Brett, ask for a runbook, status update, etc.):

## Language

- **English** for US team channels (same as other team deliverables).
- Chat with Chris can stay Spanish; the draft he pastes into Slack stays English unless he asks otherwise.

## Tone

- Sound like a real coworker: short, natural, conversational.
- Prefer “Hey Brett — …” / “quick ask” over formal openers (“Hi team,” “Hope this finds you well,” “I wanted to reach out regarding…”).
- One clear ask. Light context only — no ticket dump, no AC lists, no corporate filler.
- Avoid: “Kindly,” “Please advise,” “Per my last,” “As discussed,” bullet-heavy briefs, template blocks with labels like `Setup:` / `Verified:` (those are for Jira).
- Emojis optional and rare; never required.

## Shape

- 2–5 short sentences (or one short paragraph).
- Ticket name in plain words + id if useful; not a full description paste.
- End with a simple thanks when asking for something.

## Example

```text
Hey Brett — quick ask on PAY-XXXX (WFC AchInformation / MaxRetryAttempts).

Could you send over the QA runbook when you get a chance? I’ll run STAGE from that.

Thanks!
```
